As someone familiar with the richness and tradition of Turkish food, I knew the real test of a restaurant like this would be in the quality of their meat--and Orontes De Pijp exceeded all expectations.

The mixed grill, a hallmark of any Turkish dining experience, was a standout dish. The meat was perfectly cooked: tender, juicy, and packed with flavor that highlighted the mastery of their chefs. Every bite of lamb, chicken, and beef was full of rich, authentic taste, and it was clear that careful attention had gone into marinating and grilling the meats to perfection. The balance of spices was impeccable, enhancing the natural flavors without overwhelming them.

Beyond the food, the service was warm and attentive, delivered by a staff that clearly takes pride in their craft. The passion for food and hospitality was evident in every aspect of the meal. Whether you're a seasoned lover of Turkish cuisine or new to it, Orontes De Pijp is an unforgettable experience that transports you straight to the heart of Turkey through its remarkable dishes and genuine service. name: Loetje
description:
In de levendige Amsterdamse stadsbuurt de Pijp, is altijd wat te beleven. Tussen de mix van allerlei culturen, mensen en restaurants vind je aan de Ferdinand Bolstraat Loetje Amsterdam de Pijp. Vlakbij het Cornelis Troostplein, direct naast het politiebureau en op korte loopafstand van de RAI, Albert Cuyp en de Scheldebuurt.

Zeg je Loetje, dan zeg je de lekkerste biefstuk. Op no-nonsense wijze in echte Loetje jus, met witbrood, een royaal portie friet en salade. Bij ons geniet je van het vertrouwde biefstukreceptuur en het warme Loetje DNA.

Naast onze klassiekers hebben we bij Loetje Amsterdam de Pijp nog veel meer lekkers op de kaart. Bij ons zit je ook goed voor vis, vegetarisch en overheerlijk toetjes. Zien we je snel?

Team Loetje

name: Venster 33
description: Looking for a restaurant in Amsterdam? Look no further than Venster 33! Known for its delicious food and amazing cocktails, Venster 33 is the perfect spot to satisfy your cravings. Whether you're in the mood for Dutch cuisine or just want to grab a quick lunch, this place has got you covered. With its cozy atmosphere and friendly staff, you'll feel right at home. Located in the popular district of de Pijp, it's easily accessible and convenient. So, if you're searching for a restaurant in Amsterdam that serves good food and tasty cocktails, Venster 33 is your go-to spot!

My wife and I had been in Germany and Amsterdam for the past week, and this was our last meal before leaving. Talk about saving the best for last!
The restaurant has a cool, hip vibe. Nice and dark, but enough light to see and eat.
The menu was wide ranging, from Asian (Bao sandwiches) to Mexican ((nachos) to Dutch (Bitterballen). All of it excellent! Even the fries were the freshest, crunchiest, and tastiest we've had even in the US.
Drink menu is also extensive. They had a drink with mezcal that was smoky awesome!

name: Restaurant Zaza's
description:
Restaurant Zaza's, owned by Susie Roche from Ireland, opened its doors in May 2003 in the heart of "De Pijp", Amsterdam's Latin Quarter and hot spot for socialising. Susie and her team - Chef Cook Dave, Jasper, Noury, Ice, Gustavs and Jonah have a passion for their work and share a love of good food and great service.

Zaza's is a small, intimate restaurant with just 12 tables, serving an International menu of fresh, homemade culinary delights with influences from France, The Mediterranean and Asia which changes with the seasons.

In terms of cuisine, the dishes are refined, very well presented and perfectly quantified. In addition to the variety of the few dishes on the menu, you can feel the desire for finesse and surprise from starter to dessert. The atmosphere is subdued and very romantic, the perfect duet.

Food presentation, Service, and the FLAVORS, which top up the indulgent gastronomical feast. This is my first Michelin experience, and my family could not have chosen a better place for my induction into this exclusive experience.

The owner chef of SINNE is Swedish Greek. The pride and the personal touch shows in every aspect of your meal. SINNE means Senses in Swedish, and it's definitely an experience for all the gastronomy senses. Delicious food, plated in earthy and charming crockery, with our attentive hostess bringing new cutlery with every Course. I really should have taken a photo of the menu, to explain it all better, however the menu changes with the seasons, with a new one expected in a couple of weeks.

Our hostess was the lovely, and attentive Anna Leos (pronounced Anna Loosh) who described every detail of every dish of our Six Course meal. So there was all the finesse of gastronomy to look forward to, and we relished discovering every ingredient pop with taste on our tongues. The bartender was also very attentive, cheerful and cordial. Between him and Anna Leos, we felt very welcome guests. The photos do not do justice.

On arrival we got a complementary Amuse Bouche, actually two different presentations, which really set the bar high for what was to come. Every course promised to be my favorite, till the next one came..and our appetites and tummies were both in food heaven. Finally, it was time for our dessert. What came was another Amuse Bouche, so by the end of our meal we had enjoyed 9 Courses! Of course, the dessert was just as spectacular as the rest of our menu choices. Between us we tasted everything on the menu, and every dish was par excellence!

For me personally, it was an experience to cherish, and I would easily pay more for the food we ate, the service and the easy and relaxed ambiance of SINNE. Other members of the family enjoyed their wine, having ordered the same bottle as on their last visit here. For me there was a fabulous non alcoholic Rhubarb drink, which paired perfectly with my dessert.

name: Maris Piper Brasserie
description:
Maris Piper is a luxurious contemporary brasserie set on a beautiful corner of Frans Halsstraat in the vibrant De Pijp district, South Amsterdam.

Indulge in distinguished dishes from the brasserie menu in a relaxed but classy ambiance, with cosy private booths, an elegant open space, fireplace seating and a luminous conservatory with romantic tables for two.

We walked in (after having tried some other restaurants, but without a reservation on a Friday night...it gets difficult in Amsterdam). We were seated at the bar and gladly took it. At first I felt a bit overlooked, but our waiter quickly realized that and offered us some extra bread on the house. Normally, I wouldn't get excited about bread but the smoked almond/garlic butter they pair it with is just delicious. After a while we were even offered a table seat and continued our dinner there. The food is scrumptious!

The dishes are all prepared with care and were amazing. The wine was surprisingly well-priced and our waiters each gave us amazing warm service. Our waiter Nikos had great recommendations for the food and even for a coffee place in the morning. We felt pampered all evening. I can greatly recommend the smoked eel and foie gras, the scallops and ribeye. Don't forget to order a side of mashed potato with bone marrow- it is really good.

I was even surprised about the desserts; sometimes it can be an afterthought, but at Maris Piper each dessert was well balanced and brought their own personality. Whether you're a local or visiting, Pekelhaarring promises a refined and memorable dining experience. Highly recommended! name: Cannibale Royale Ruysdael
description:
Cannibale Royale, brasserie extraordinaire fulfills all needs for anyone who loves good food, lots of meat, exotic beers and the most beautiful wines. Cannibale Royale is a bar where you can feel like a prehistoric being again. You are always welcome to drop by for a delicious cocktail or special beer to compliment our meaty treats.
Forget all hypes about haute cuisine for a minute, it's time to enjoy everything that is tasteful, rich in flavour and is just simply good.

Un bisou de Cannibale Royale!

We are sorry to hear about the confusion regarding your reservation.
After your contact person filed the request for a group reservation, we sent multiple emails and tried calling him several times to confirm the reservation, but unfortunately, we did not receive any response from him. As a result, we were unable to finalize the reservation and we assumed you were not interested in making the reservation anymore.
Given these efforts to contact your contact person and confirm your reservation, we were quite surprised to see four 1-star reviews from you and your guests. We feel this rating does not reflect the efforts we made to reach out and secure your reservation. We understand your disappointment upon arrival, but we hope you can also see our perspective and reconsider the fairness of these reviews.

We are glad to hear that another restaurant could accommodate you.

Our apologies that you feel this way and that we could not solve this the same night.

name: LOCALS All Day Brunch
description: Looking for a delightful brunch experience in Amsterdam? Look no further than LOCALS All Day Brunch! Our cozy coffee shop offers a variety of delicious breakfast and brunch options, as well as mouth-watering lunch dishes. From classic eggs Benedict to unique avocado toast creations, there's something for everyone on our menu. Plus, our coffee is some of the best in town! Whether you're a local or just passing through, come enjoy a relaxing meal at LOCALS All Day Brunch. Located conveniently near many the Museum Quarter and other restaurants and shops, we're the perfect spot for a mid-day break. Stop by today and taste the difference!

name: Graham's Kitchen
description: Experience the warmth of authentic casual fine dining at Graham's Kitchen in Amsterdam. Delight in a personalised culinary experience by Chef Graham Mee, complemented by friendly service and great wine. Indulge in seasonal specialities amidst a welcoming ambience, creating unforgettable memories in the heart of the Netherlands. From succulent seafood creations to mouthwatering meat selections and vibrant vegetarian options, there is something to cater to every palate. Whether it's a romantic dinner for two, a group celebration or a private dining event, we always provide a warm and welcoming ambience that makes every guest feel part of the family. name: Brasserie Lolita
description: Are you looking for a restaurant in Amsterdam? Look no further than Brasserie Lolita in de Pijp! This gezellig French restaurant is the perfect restaurant in Amsterdam. With delicious French dishes and a cozy atmosphere, it's the perfect spot to enjoy a meal with friends or family. Plus, it's located in the heart of Amsterdam Zuid, de Pijp, making it a great hotspot for all your dining needs. Join for the best dinner or come for some of the best cocktails and have fun at the bar. Brasserie Lolita is well known in Amsterdam and the hotspot for the locals in de Pijp. If you are looking for a French restaurant right in the heart of de Pijp Amsterdam, come check out Brasserie Lolita today! Open till 3am on weekend days.

The restaurant boasts a great ambiance that immediately puts you at ease. The friendly personnel, all of them exuding a warm smile and welcoming attitude, made the evening even more enjoyable.

The food itself was a delight. Notably, the prices were reasonable.

Casa Nostra offers a variety of typical dishes. Being surrounded by almost all Italian staff truly made me feel like I was right at home.

The interior of the restaurant was a tad smaller than expected, leading to a somewhat noisy environment that occasionally made it challenging to maintain a focused conversation.

My only significant point of improvement was with the seating. Despite making reservations in advance, my party was assigned higher-than-average bar stools, which deviated from my preferred seating type. It would be fantastic if Casa Nostra considers offering a choice of seating options in the future.

The outside terrace exuded a charming and cozy ambiance, making it an attractive option for pleasant weather.

I'll definitely be returning for another taste of Italy in Amsterdam!","published_at":"a year ago","published_at_date":"2023-08-18T12:27:33","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":1,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMX-BYznb4lFRKbHdRYJpyaKbq25zs3sOEYINOw=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP2LiSl2AntujwZ7nEZLsmGDoNn5DxBhluh4yn1=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPz3gUQKkJXDlUsbIzstscZRqVPGRBNWvXg7PBI=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipN0tM6JG3Z2S-4EeFSCGKIMRtspXzw_3bNSANqE=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMJYF7vJWxCSeEksWofb3q1StvjJctPYDv3C2tk=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURycXJhN0RREAE","rating":5,"name":"Ivan Stepanin","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115033518195396383436?hl=en-GB","review_text":"One of the best Italian restaurants in Amsterdam. name: Maydanoz
description:
Ontdek de geheimen van de Turkse keuken.Smaken waar je blij van wordt.
Maydanoz is een mediterraan restaurant in Amsterdam waar de Turkse keuken centraal staat, met een menu dat zowel vleesliefhebbers als vegetariers en veganisten aanspreekt.
De gerechten worden bereid met de beste ingredienten en weerspiegelen de rijke diversiteit van de mediterrane keuken.
Van traditionele kebab tot verfijnde vegetarische schotels, bij Maydanoz is er voor elke smaakpapil wel iets te vinden. Uw nieuwe favoriete plek voor tapas in Amsterdam! Onze uitgebreide tapaskaart biedt een heerlijke mix van koude en warme hapjes, geinspireerd op de Turkse en Mediterrane keuken. Deel kleine gerechtjes met vrienden of familie en ontdek de veelzijdigheid van onze smaken.

name: Ranchi Amsterdam
description: Ranchi Amsterdam is the spot for Japanese-style sandwiches. We offer different kinds of katsu sandwiches, Japanese sodas and homemade drinks. Our ton katsu is made with locally sourced pork. Ranchi Amsterdam means lunch Amsterdam in Japanese, we made it our mission to serve the best sandwiches possible. You want your lunch to go, or order via uber eats or thuisbezorgd. For lunchen, sandwich, sandwiches or brunch Amsterdam please visit us. But also coffee near me or lunch to go, Ranchi Amsterdam is the best restaurant near me. Also restaurant takeaway in restaurant de Pijp we are the right place because we have restaurant lunch and we are a takeaway restaurant. We hope to see you in our location to lunch Amsterdam.

name: FACTORY GIRL Brunch Restaurant
description: Discover FACTORY GIRL Brunch, a breakfast and lunch restaurant located in the local area of De Pijp. Enjoy our delicious breakfast, brunch, and lunch options served all day. Begin your day with our mouthwatering all-day breakfast choices, including healthy gluten-free pancakes. Explore our best vegan breakfast dishes, indulge in our range of avocado sandwiches, and treat yourself to our vegetarian bruschetta options. We also provide gluten-free and sugar-free items on our menu. Our speciality coffees are made with ethically sourced beans, ensuring a unique and delightful taste. Join us at Factory Girl Amsterdam in the bohemian De Pijp district of Amsterdam for an artistic food experience..

{"question":"Hello,
Do you have Vegan options for Lunch? ","answer":"Hello Caterina, 
Thank you for asking. We do have very delicious vegan options for Lunch. I will recomend you two of my favorite dishes in the menu. There are more options, as well

LA DE DAH hummus, avocado, mashed beetroot
IN DER MITTE avocado, black cumin seeds, chiaseeds, red beans, mashed beetroot.
It's all come with bio organic sourdough bread. I am sure that you will love the taste. 
We hope to host you soon. 
Best

name: Restaurant Le Hollandais
description:
Le Hollandais staat voor verfijnd koken met lef maar respect voor het product, waar de gast meegenomen wordt in het culinaire proces. Er wordt uitsluitend gekookt met verse producten van hoogwaardige kwaliteit.
Wij onderscheiden ons in de Amsterdamse horeca door op hoog gastronomisch niveau te koken maar tegelijkertijd toegankelijk te zijn voor ieder. Het echte bistro-gevoel. Het klassiek Franse menu met een moderne twist verandert elke paar weken om u te blijven verrassen

name: Franggo De Pijp
description:
Rooted on the African islands of Cape Verde where our grandfather was born, our family spread all along Portugal. We as a father and daughter moved to Amsterdam where we decided to start our experience into our concept of Franggo.

At Franggo we serve authentic Portuguese Flame Grilled Chicken influenced by african touches. We believe in transforming this original product to modern times with urban vibes. Our core values are to serve the best chicken fast, in a cool ambiance, offering the best prices. By doing so Franggo is one big happy family.

Authentic Portuguese flamed chicken. Juicy, tender, intact not burnt skin. Cooked to order. Really well done.
Sauces are available. It's so good you don't even need one.
The salad is also as Portuguese as it can gets. Forget the soggy lettuce, here you will get flavorful red tomato, well seasoned with oregano and olive oil.
We didn't had the fries, but the piri-piri ones are famous. If that's your thing, try them. Franggo cannot do wrong.
Unpretentious place, friendly service.
They also offer take-away.
Alcoholic drinks are not served.

We came here based on the reviews and boy, we were not disappointed. The overall vibe of the place is pretty nice and calm, the place has an aesthetic to it that is really unique. Orders are placed downstairs and the seating is upstairs where you have a view of the entrance. We ordered 2 Franggo menu 2 Half chicken with mix sauce (peri-peri/garlic butter lemon) and a side of rice and jacket potato. We waited for around 7 mins the food arrived the chicken tasted amazing tender and well-done with that sauce, it wasn't very spicy for us but had pleasant mild heat and a kick of sour from the lemon in the sauce. The jacket potato was really tasty as well it was dressed with butter lemon and herbs. The rice to my surprise had a distinctive flavour that reminded me of the my mom's rice I ate back home, I couldn't resist to eat it in its own, you can also drizzle on some of the sauce that comes with the chicken 

Important to mention, the staff are really nice and friendly and the service was amazing. The waiter served us 2 pieces of Pastel de nata to make up for  "long wait" which was only 7 mins (we definitely waited more than that in previous experiences) a gesture I really appreciated from the staff and tells that they really care.
We finished with the our free pastel de natas which were creamy form the inside with crusty flaky crust. I highly recommend getting one when you visit.
I will definitely be back on my next visit to Amsterdam.","published_at":"a year ago","published_at_date":"2023-08-12T17:41:39","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":1,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP4H5o46djasgE3DSxIDFkSvDqNSVq29lyFywez=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipM-GLkBE53UKkZYFyXNjTsoLFs91BhDXf53tIp0=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP85qqecHx23JKWavhGjyAGhcdWXY3mFlBAgepZ=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNJ0vbEKdmjb6kgtLlFX-HaXMzyaaG3n-Kv9mVz=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPb9md8psGjcBlG5bJkafpRWHAwNpTTqh2NyklH=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNma3FyVURREAE","rating":5,"name":"Archil Kublashvili","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117910002649918621563?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Really nice spot, relaxing atmosphere with nothing fancy, yet cozy enough to feel yourself in the center of Lisbon.

name: Vegan Junk Food Bar
description: Located at Marie Heinekenplein, also known, the Quartier Latin of Amsterdam you will find this awesome restaurant. Close by there are hotspots as The Heineken Brewery and the Albert Cuyp market within a 5-minute walk from the restaurant. Enjoy our #PLANETFRIENDLY #FUTURISTIC and #JUICY takes while sipping on an extraordinary cocktail in a scenery filled with graffiti walls, Hip Hop, R&B music and street art.

name: Spaghetteria
description: Geniet van een authentieke Italiaanse ervaring bij Spaghetteria Caffe, een van de beste restaurants in Amsterdam. Of u nu op zoek bent naar een traditioneel Italiaans diner of een snelle lunch in Amsterdam, Spaghetteria Caffe is de perfecte plek. Proef de heerlijke pasta's, bereid met verse, lokale ingredienten. Dit restaurant is een favoriet onder de lokale bevolking en toeristen voor zijn authentieke eten en gezellige sfeer. Ervaar de ware essentie van Amsterdamse eetgelegenheden terwijl u geniet van de heerlijke smaken van de Italiaanse keuken. Dus waar wacht u nog op? Bezoek vandaag nog Spaghetteria Caffe en ontdek waarom het wordt beschouwd als een van de beste Italiaanse restaurants in Amsterdam.

name: Bar Mash
description:
Bar MASH is a tiny bar, with a spacious sunny terrace in the centre of the buzzing Amsterdam Pijp neighborhood, just off the Albert Cuyp market.
At MASH we serve a rather small, carefully selected quality range of beers, wines and cocktails, chefs Air & Mem cook up awesome Thai dishes and snacks, bold beautiful flavours guaranteed.
MASH is opened daily from 12.00 PM to 1.00 AM, no reservations, just come by!
Looking forward seeing you around!
Team MASH

name: Le Smash Amsterdam | De Pijp
description:
Le Smash Amsterdam | De Pijp is the go-to restaurant for people craving hamburgers and comfort food. Famous for serving the most-loved burgers in Amsterdam, we specialize in crafting the perfect Smash Burger - a crispy, juicy, flavor-packed bite you won't forget! Whether you're in the mood for a classic, a special or a veggie smash burger that doesn't compromise on taste, we've got something for everyone. Plus, all our burgers are 100% halal, making it a welcoming spot for all food enthusiasts. Whether you're looking for lunch, dinner or takeout, we're open everyday of the week.

Hungry yet? Stop by our restaurant and taste the hype for yourself! Don't forget to add our delicious fries and shakes. Your next favorite burger awaits!

name: MOAK Pancakes Pijp
description:
Welcome to Moak, your go-to spot for an all-day brunch experience in Amsterdam.
From fluffy pancakes and savory toasts to freshly prepared eggs and hearty breakfast plates, paired with coffee and vibrant juices, we've got something for everyone at any time of the day.

Immerse yourself in our cozy atmosphere, where smooth hip-hop tunes from our vinyl collection set the perfect vibe. Whether you're catching up with friends, taking a break, or starting your day right, the beats and flavors at Moak will keep you coming back.

Come see why Moak is one of the top-rated breakfast and brunch destinations in Amsterdam!

I had high hopes for this restaurant, but unfortunately, our experience was far from enjoyable. The main issue was the rude behavior of one of the waiters who wasn't serving us directly but was the one who seated us at our table. When we were leaving, he insisted on closing the door, presumably because of the cold. The problem? My child was still inside, and we hadn't exited yet! It was an unnecessary and rude interaction that really soured the entire experience.

On top of that, the service was overall disappointing. It felt like we were invisible to the staff, possibly because we came with children. It seemed like they had little patience for our kids, who, of course, didn't eat the food like adults. They were expected to sit quietly without any leeway, and when they pulled out a snack they same rude waiter told us it wasn't allowed. I get it, but it's kids. Why wouldn't you have something for kids then to order? It's impossible to order 3-4 course meal for kids with snails. It's frustrating when a family-friendly atmosphere is missing, and you're treated like an inconvenience.

Additionally, I never been served a food where the waiter just pass me the plate and I have to put it on the table on my own. Come on is it restaurant recommended by Michelin guide or a fast food chain where they don't pay attention on how they serve the food?! If you a restaurant it's a huge mistake and unacceptable.

As for the food, it was just okay--not terrible, but nothing memorable either. Given the lack of hospitality and the general unwelcoming vibe, I honestly don't think it's worth the visit if you're in Amsterdam! We were really looking forward to a great meal and a pleasant experience, but sadly it's just not the case. 1) service is much better than the average service in Amsterdam.

Just cause not everyone knows the culture as a foreigner , they don't have to be rude about things.

I bought a beer there cause I went to the Heineken experience and it was my lucky day, they closed early for an emergency that night. I went across the street for a beer.

The tables are old and ratted so I don't understand the attitude problem. But when I put my beer on the table , the waiter sprinted to me with a bothered look and grabbed my beer, and slammed it down on a coaster to prove a point. To use the coasters.  There was loud music playing and many many people . Maybe he was overwhelmed.

Why couldn't he just say so kindly . Use his words instead of his passive-aggressive body language.  He walked away and didn't even say anything to me after doing that . Like it was my purpose to ruin his night by not knowing that they WANTED TO USE card board coasters on the old dirty tables.

It's literally run down. No new decor. I thought it was the actually vibe of the place. The wooden tables and chairs with no cloths. Barely any lighting.  I chose it cause it looked less fancy than the other 20 restaurants in the area that sell Heineken.

After that interaction, I left and didn't bother ordering food. It was my first time there . No one is walking into restaurants choosing to be rude. Waiters need to stop acting like foreigners are traveling just to irk them. name: Coffee & Coconuts.
description: Coffee & Coconuts is a cafe and coffee roastery with its heart beating on island rhythms. We aim to live by the currents, plan by the tides, and follow the sun. Any time of the year you can enjoy young coconuts, great coffee and colourfull plates of food. Sit back and breathe in the calming vibe of - or what seems to be - your ultimate holiday break.

name: Serre
description: Serre restaurant offers a versatile culinary experience within the hotel. Whether it's a morning coffee, a delightful lunch or a leisurely dinner, Serre welcomes you throughout the day. The charming summer terrace offers the perfect backdrop for outdoor dining and afternoon beverages. Led by Chef Bram Postel, Serre proudly holds a Michelin Bib Gourmand, a testament to its commitment to offering high-quality cuisine at moderate prices.

name: Wild & The Moon
description:
Wild & The Moon is a movement created by a tribe of lovers of life, nature, and good food, chefs, nutritionists, and naturopaths who seek to share their way of life and think above all that real food is food that's good for you, good for the planet, and delicious.

From breakfast to dinner, from delicious healthy light to healthy streetfood. There is something for everyone! Take a look at our menu! C U soon!

We did walk-in around 7.50pm but surprisingly it's still full of people. There were 4 queues ahead of us so we had to wait around 20 mins. Luckily I was there to chitchat with my friend so it made our waiting time shorter.

name: Miri Mary Indian Restaurant Amsterdam
description: Discover a blend of tradition and innovation at Miri Mary Indian Restaurant Amsterdam. A premier Indian Restaurant in De Pijp that combines the soul of India with the personality of Amsterdam. Our menu elegantly combines the rich flavours of India with modern culinary finesse. Experience a unique dinner or lunch where global classics meet Indian spices, enhanced by our speciality coffee and handcrafted cocktails. Join us in Amsterdam for a brunch, lunch or dinner and embark on a memorable journey through the diverse tapestry of Indian cuisine. At Miri Mary, every meal is a celebration of life and flavour. Visit us in Amsterdam's vibrant De Pijp neighbourhood for an unforgettable dining experience or pop by for a drink at our cocktail bar.

featured_reviews:
[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNmNzRfaTh3RRAB","rating":5,"name":"Quisha Martin","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107845896133672573710?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I had brunch here with friends after making a 2 p.m. reservation. Surprisingly, the place wasn't very busy, with only three other tables occupied, which I didn't expect given the positive things I'd heard about it.

We were seated and greeted promptly, but the service afterward was disappointing. Despite having so few customers, it took some time for anyone to come and take our order. There seemed to be only two staff members working--one at the counter and one serving tables--but I didn't expect it to take so long, especially considering how quiet it was. We eventually had to call the waiter ourselves to let them know we were ready, which felt odd since most restaurants check in with you after some time.

Adding to the inattentiveness, a nearby table that had finished eating before we arrived still had dirty plates left on it even when we left, which gave the impression of poor attention to detail.

That said, the food was absolutely delicious and saved the experience for us. Every dish we ordered was well-prepared and enjoyable. However, great food alone isn't enough when the service feels this unorganized.

I'd still recommend this place for the food, but I hope they work on improving their service. This South African micro brewery was an unexpected gem. After finishing the Heineken tour just a short walk away, my wife and I set out to find some local craft beer--and we couldn't have picked a better spot.

We ordered a flight featuring the Cape Point Pilsner, Hazy IPA, Watermelon Wheat, and English Ale. Each beer brought something unique to the table, and all were absolutely fantastic!

Watermelon Wheat (Flagship): Perfectly
balanced, not too sweet, with just the right hint of fruit.

English Ale: A smooth, subtle caramel flavor that felt both rich and light.

Cape Point Pilsner: Surprisingly refreshing; its slightly sour aroma gave way to one of the best pilsners I've ever tasted.

Hazy IPA: An excellent balance of citrusy brightness and just the right amount of bitterness.

While we didn't try the food, if it's even half as good as the beer, it's sure to be a hit. For any beer lover visiting Amsterdam, this spot is a must!","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-13T15:06:47","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPiBw-9yIANonFVqMloWw4jKZRpxHwnSsCakPI_=s1024"]}]

name: Blue Dragon
description:
Traditional ambiance, relaxed design interior, refined taste, is this what you are looking for in a Japanese Fusion lunch or dining experience?
Then come to our new restaurant Blue Dragon on the Marie Heinekenplein in the hotspot de Pijp Amsterdam and enjoy the Sushi Fusion All You Can Eat or A La Carte concept with us.
We would like to invite you to a relaxing journey of sushi fusion feast. Our extensive menu consists of more than a hundred different dishes of high quality. Enjoy our delicious drinking menu with many Cocktails and Mocktails. These will be introduced to you by our friendly and experienced colleagues to ensure that anyone who spends their "quality time" here at Blue Dragon - will have an unforgettable experience.

I recently visited Sushito via ClassPass on May 28th, but accidentally placed my order at the wrong location. When I arrived, I politely asked the waitress behind the bar if she could call the other location to see if anything could be done. She was incredibly polite and promptly checked with the chef manager in the kitchen.

To my utter shock, the Italian chef came out and began yelling at me, insisting that nothing could be done about my mistake. He continued to scream, even as I stood there in disbelief at his reaction. I calmly asked him to stop, but he persisted. The staff, who appeared just as shocked as I was, looked on helplessly.

I informed the chef that his behavior had cost them a loyal customer who had previously enjoyed many visits to Sushito. I have worked in the hospitality industry for ten years and have never encountered such unprofessional and aggressive conduct from a staff member.

This experience has completely soured my view of Sushito, and I will not be returning.  The extreme rudeness and lack of basic customer service were appalling. If you value respectful and polite service, I would recommend looking elsewhere.

I understand that "no" is an answer, but the rudeness of the delivery really shocked me.","published_at":"7 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-05-28T19:26:11","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":[]}]

description: Eat the Rainbow! At Rainbowls Amsterdam - Acai | Matcha | Coffee | Juices, we care about healthy food that's not only nutritious but also most delicious. We're open everyday of the week, to serve Amsterdam their beloved coffee, breakfast, brunch, lunch or afternoon snack. Take a seat and relax or pick-up your order on the go!

name: Het Paardje
description: Het Paardje is een geliefde bar en bistro, al meer dan 17 jaar een vaste waarde in de bruisende wijk De Pijp. Geniet van ons ruime terras op het levendige Gerard Douplein, waar je zowel in de zomer als in de winter terecht kunt voor een ontspannen borrel, een uitgebreide lunch of een sfeervol diner. Als restaurant met een ongedwongen sfeer en een gezellig cafe-karakter, bieden wij een gevarieerd menu en een uitstekende plek voor elke gelegenheid. Of je nu komt voor een vrijdagmiddagborrel, een groepsdiner of gewoon om te genieten van het beste terras van Amsterdam, bij Het Paardje ben je aan het juiste adres!

name: Arles
description:
Arles is a modern bistro located in a quiet side street of the Amsterdamse Pijp. Just like in the Parisian 'bistronomy' scene, you will find creative dishes in an accessible and artistic environment.

 Numa Muller, our chef from Arles, creates a new 4 and 5 course chef's menu every month (a la carte is also possible). His neo-bistro dishes are surprising because of the special combinations of French cuisine with outside influences.

 We have an entirely French wine list with an interesting composition of traditional producers, as well as emerging vins nature.

The restaurant has held a Michelin Bib-Gourmand since 2018.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzby1lTjN3RRAB","rating":4,"name":"Enrico Verdolotti","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104445347436213521651?hl=en-GB","review_text":"The restaurant boasts a beautiful and welcoming atmosphere, paired with excellent service. The staff is professional, friendly, and well-informed, creating an enjoyable dining experience.

However, I was somewhat disappointed with the food, especially considering the price. We opted for the chef's five-course tasting menu, which included three appetizers, one main course, and a dessert.

The first two appetizers were outstanding, the scallop, and the mushrooms in chestnut cream; but the third, a fried croquette, felt uninspired, with the flavor dominated entirely by the frying. The main course, featuring venison, was delicious; however, the addition of two small pieces of eel felt out of place and did not harmonize with the rest of the dish.

The most disappointing aspect, unfortunately, was the dessert. The menu included a pear-based dessert accompanied by parsley ice cream. While innovative, the flavors were peculiar and didn't align with what one would expect for a dessert course. Unsatisfied, I asked to try the second dessert option, which was cottage cheese-based. Sadly, this too failed to impress and did not feel like a fitting conclusion to an otherwise refined meal. For the price I paid I would have expected more.

In summary, while the menu shows great promise, certain elements could be improved. I would strongly recommend revisiting the dessert selection to ensure a more satisfying ending to an otherwise well-thought-out dining experience.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-18T11:51:55","response_from_owner_text":"Hey there, Enrico Verdolotti! name: Restaurant JA
description: Looking for a fine dining experience in Amsterdam? Look no further than Restaurant JA in De Pijp. Run by a couple without any staff, this intimate restaurant offers a warm and inviting atmosphere perfect for a date night or dinner with friends. Rated as one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam, serving up dishes made with seasonal vegetables, fresh North Sea fish, and local Dutch ingredients infused with French and Japanese cuisine. And don't forget to pair your meal with one of their classic or natural wines for the ultimate dining experience. Come see why Restaurant JA is a must-visit destination for foodies in Amsterdam.

The setting is cozy and romantic, with an open kitchen and nine round wooden tables that give off a true "at-home" vibe. You sit right in the open kitchen and get to watch the chef prepare each dish of the tasting menu--a wonderful, immersive experience!

The menu is full of delightful surprises--from the Sake Panna Cotta, which is a silky, slightly sweet starter, to the Saffron Brioche Feuilletee that feels indulgent yet light. A standout dish has to be the North Sea Crab, which you can elevate with a supplement of Perle Imperial Caviar. It's seafood perfection, but at a price! The Nigiri Langoustine keeps things playful and interesting, and the Dry Aged Turbot with Sambelzu has incredible depth of flavor. Even the Seaweed Dessert is a conversation starter--something unexpected but totally fitting with the meal.

For EU77.50, this creative menu offers great value for its unique ingredients and intimate experience. Restaurant Ja is the perfect spot for a special night out or if you're craving something a bit different in Amsterdam's dining scene!","published_at":"3 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-10-03T15:25:08","response_from_owner_text":"Thank you so much for your wonderful review! name: Badeta Koffiebranders de Pijp
description:
Specialty coffee bar + winkel in De Pijp, Amsterdam. Je kunt bij ons terecht voor een goede bak koffie die wij met zorg hebben uitgezocht en gebrand in onze branderij. We hebben altijd twee soorten koffies op de malers, zo is er voor ieder wat wils!
Daarnaast verkopen wij hier alle producten die je in onze online webshop kunt vinden.
Om onze sfeer en koffie zo goed mogelijk tot zijn recht te laten komen hebben wij gekozen voor een laptop vrij cafe. Geniet van de koffie en het moment!

name: NAZKA
description: NAZKA brings modern Peruvian cuisine to life, celebrated globally for its vibrant fusion of flavors and ingredients. Guests are treated to extraordinary dishes, imaginative wine pairings, and expertly crafted cocktails in a relaxed, cosmopolitan atmosphere. Recognized by patrons, food lovers, and critics, NAZKA is featured in both the Michelin Guide and Gault&Millau Guide. Chef Koosh Kothari, trained by Virgilio Martinez of Lima's Central--ranked No. 1 on the World's 50 Best list in 2023--brings innovation and depth to each creation. Conveniently located in Amsterdam's trendy De Pijp neighborhood, NAZKA is accessible via public transport from both RAI Station and Amsterdam Central.

name: Surya Amsterdam | Indian & Nepalese restaurant & bar
description:
Surya Restaurants - Indiaas/Nepalees restaurant & bar.
Houdt u van een authentieke Indiase maaltijd die u even in India doet wanen? Bent u op zoek naar een locatie om met een partner, vriend of uw familie lekker uit eten te gaan? Kom dan van heerlijke Indiase gerechten genieten bij Surya Restaurants! . Wie benieuwd is naar de Indiase en/of Nepalese keuken is bij ons op het juiste adres. Als Indiaas/Nepalees restaurant in Amsterdam leveren wij culinair meesterschap en staan wij bekend om onze uitstekende service. Geniet van een overheerlijke curry, van smaakvolle tandoori of masala gerechten.

name: Pind Punjabi
description:
Pind Punjabi is an Indian restaurant located at Van Woustraat 240, 1073 NC Amsterdam (Nearby station Rai) and Tram 4 stop (Amstelkade) is right in front of the restaurant.
Pind Punjabi Restaurant offers a unique dining experience with a relaxing environment, spacious enough to easily accommodate 72 guests. We serve Authentic Indian Vegetarian, Vegan, and Non-vegetarian (100% Halal) dishes.

Pind Punjabi Restaurant offers a wide variety of dishes prepared with original Indian recipes and make use of Authentic clay oven (Tandoor) and fresh ingredients. Many dedicated customers come from all over Amsterdam and The Netherlands to experience the unforgettable taste of traditional Indian food.

Welcome to Pind Punjabi!

name: De Waaghals
description:
De sfeer in Vegetarisch Restaurant De Waaghals is informeel, de keuken verfijnd en creatief. Er wordt een 3- of 4-gangen
verrassingsmenu geserveerd met gerechten die zijn geinspireerd door de kookkunst uit de hele wereld. We maken geen gebruik van vlees-vervangende producten, maar creeren gerechten van de groenten uit het seizoen, die zoveel mogelijk lokaal worden geoogst. Het menu wisselt regelmatig met het seizoen mee. De Waaghals bestaat al sinds 1981 en word nog steeds bezocht door zowel vegetariers, veganisten en alles eters!

name: Tulsi Indian Restaurant
description:
Tulsi Indiaas restaurant is een fine dining Indiaas restaurant gevestigd op Van Woustraat 212, 1073 NA, Amsterdam en Amsterdam Centrum (Nieuwezijds Voorburgwal 34,1012 SB Amsterdam). Wij van hartewelkom om teontspannenkomen, socialis eren en tedelen goede tijden met je familie en vrienden op Tulsi Indian restaurant.

Tulsi restaurant serveer vers bereide authentieke meest populaire Indiase starters zoals Chola Bhatura, Golgappas / PaniPuri, Aloo Tikki, Aloo paprichaat etc. Tulsi restaurant biedtook de verscheidenheid aan andere vegetarisch, niet-vegetarischen tandoori grill gerechten. De gerechten worden bereid door onzeprofessionele chef-koks met meerdan 20 jaar ervaringen .

name: Got Cha Asian Cafe
description:
Hihi,
We are a low-sugar bubble tea cafe and Asian bakery.
Plenty of choices for Asian soft breads, desserts and Hongkong Egg Waffle(Ji Dan Zi) .
We make fluffy chiffon cakes (low sugar No butter, birthday cake available for pre-order, check our Instagram for more flavors).
Hmmm, We also have the most complete flavors of Japanese Ice Cream scoops in the Netherlands!
Dine-in and USB sockets Available inside.
Hope to see you soon!

name: Brouwerij Troost
description:
In 2013 bouwden we onze eerste brouwerij in een voormalig klooster in De Pijp. We startten met 3 soorten bier die je in de aanliggende pub kon drinken. De jaarcapaciteit was 100.000 liter en dat werd allemaal ter plekke opgedronken. In 2015 vergrootte we de productie capaciteit met een nieuwe brouwerij op het Westergasterrein. Momenteel is Brouwerij Troost De Pijp de plek waar we experimenteren, nieuwe bieren ontwikkelen en de bieren met kleine oplages produceren.

Bij bier moet goed gegeten worden en dat kan ook bij Brouwerij Troost. De keuken van Brouwerij Troost De Pijp is open tot 22:30 uur om de lekkerste hamburgers, salades, bitterballen, Libanese pizettes, nacho's, cheesecakes en nog heel veel meer voor je te maken.

The Service is excellent, starting from a nice welcome by the waiter from the reception. We were there to celebrate our anniversary. The waiter first confirmed our reservation and congrats to us. During the diner, the staff are friendly, checking with us is everything okay, how is the serving speed, would we like to have a chill break before having the dessert etc. Right before we left, the staff congrats us again, really sweet. Our chief is great, she is kind, keep smiling while I cannot imagine how heavy the work she is doing, constantly cooking for us for 3 hours almost.

The Atmosphere is really great too. It has soft lighting, decorated with traditional Japanese style.

Now come to the most important part for me. The FOOD, it is amazing. We chose the Classic menu.
* Started with Tuna tataki (I am too focus on the food and forgot to take picture for it). It has beautifully caramelized crust but super tender inside.
* Then come with Seasalt crusted sea bass. The crust looks interesting too, it looks like puffed pancake, asked the chief, it is 90% salf and 10% whisked egg. The fish filet stays juicy with the Seasalt crust on top. The chief bake the fish skin separately, make it super crispy (I love chips, also fish chips)
* The 3rd course is Canadian lobster with Yuzu garlic butter. Beside those 3 words: lobster + garlic + butter, what do we need to say more. (Spoil alert: it come with the fire show)
* Wagyu steak is definitely the high light of the course. It come with 3 "sauce", himalayan salt, Japanese wasabi and one more (I forgot the name, but that's my favorite match with the Wagyu among all 3) Its provide a bit freshness to compensate well with the grease of Waygu. Btw it come with grilled zucchini and paprika too (I love grilled vegetables!!!!) It also come with some baked Wagyu fat part too. I expect it would be crispy, but the bigger pieces is not crispy enough though (small details)
* The Chicken fried rice served together with the Wagyu. Do not get my wrong, it is tasty too, but having it together with Wagyu, I could not finish it eventually. Personally I am not a fan of having rice together with steam
* The desert: Sazanka pancake (Dorayaki, one my favorite sweets, I love red bean paste ) the Japanese ice cream served with it is Matcha icecream. Personally, I do not like dessert to be too sweet, so leave the syrup aside. The Dorayaki is perfect with Matcha together
* Extra: we also got an extra dessert on the house for the Congratulation","published_at":"5 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-07-22T19:36:43","response_from_owner_text":"Dear Ruiling Zhang,

name: Pazzi De Pijp
description: Bij Pazzi Amsterdam, geniet je in een warme Italiaanse sfeer van overheerlijke gerechten en dranken. Sinds 2010 bereidt onze vakkundige pizzaiolo volgens traditioneel receptuur verse houtovenpizza's. Ieder gerecht wordt bereidt met eerlijke en zorgvuldig gekozen producten, en dat proef je! Laat je verrassen door de echte Italiaanse antipasti, pizza's en desserts geserveerd met veel passie en trots. Kom langs bij Pazzi in Amsterdam en proef het echte Italie. Geen zin om te koken? Haal je favoriete pizza bij ons af!

I enjoy also bake pizzas myself, thanks to my humble culinary background, so I know what a pizza has to be and how is made to obtain certain results.

I will not spend corny words like you see often in the reviews here on Google, but let me say one thing, this is no doubt, easily one of the best pizza I ever had in my life, truly.

The dough is truly amazing, so tasty and delicate, that melts in your mouth after every bite.

Quality-wise, top tier ingredients make this pizza a truly special meal for anyone that wants to try what a modern style Neapolitan pizza means, without flying in Naples.

Bravo to you Dope, I wasn't expecting that much to be honest, I am impressed.

P.s. Next to Dope, there is another pizza place, I am not saying the name, but compared to Dope, it's not worth it, believe me.

name: Sir Pita
description:
At Sir Pita, we pour our passion into creating mouthwatering pita sandwiches, made fresh with the finest ingredients.

Located in de Pijp, one of Amsterdam's trendiest neighborhood, our menu features a variety of Middle Eastern pitas: super crispy green Falafel, hearty aubergine Sabich & roasted chicken with a unique homemade spice mix.

Whether you're looking for a quick lunch on the go or a satisfying meal to savor, Sir Pita offers a perfect blend of tradition and taste. Swing by today and savor the magic where authentic recipes blend seamlessly with modern convenience

When I arrived at the restaurant, I was quickly checked in and led to my table. I had a wonderful seat with a direct view of the Japanese garden and pond in the back of the hotel.  It was very serene and peaceful.

The service here is impeccable, and the food is superb. Every server here is from Japan dressed in Kimono's adding to the ambiance.  I was just in Sapporo and Tokyo earlier this year, and the fish here was also just as fresh and flavorful as in Japan, too.  The Wagyu was cooked to perfection and melted in my mouth. I would highly recommend upgrading to the Icho Kaiseki menu. It will elevate the Omakase experience to a whole new level.

name: Sababa Amsterdam De Pijp
description: Onze keuken, geinspireerd door het Midden-Oosten, biedt hoogwaardig, eerlijk geprijsd eten. Van vegan en vegetarisch tot onze biologische shawarma, ontdek een wereld van heerlijke smaken. Snelle service in een ontspannen sfeer. Sababa nodigt je uit om onze huisgemaakte falafel te komen proeven en te genieten van een culinaire reis vol gezonde en smakelijke verrassingen!

name: De Pizzakamer
description:
De Pizzakamer is een kleine maar gezellige pizzeria in het hart van De Pijp waar Amsterdammers samenkomen om te genieten van traditionele Italiaanse pizza. Een ruim terras maakt de lange zomeravonden onvergetelijk, terwijl de industriele binnenruimte voor een gezellige sfeer zorgt in de winter.

 De Pizzakamer is a small but cozy pizzeria in the heart of De Pijp where Amsterdammers get together to enjoy traditional Italian pizza. A spacious terrace makes the long summer nights unforgettable, while the industrial indoor area creates a cozy atmosphere to keep you warm in the winter time.

name: Calle Ocho
description:
The best Miami streetfood restaurant land ate-night cocktailbar in the Pijp area in Amsterdam.

Calle Ocho: a warm, fun and buzzy ambience with some "gekkigheid". A place where you can take your tinder-date, grandmother or your volleyball team.

From Cuban to Mexican and from Caribbean to Tex-Mex. Calle Ocho is all of that in a nutshell. Our chefs translated this to a small menu which changes regularly.

name: Impero Romano Amsterdam
description: Enjoy the traditional and original Italian cuisine in Amsterdam at ristorante Impero Romano! Immerse yourself in the Mediterranean atmosphere and taste the real Italy in our restaurant. A large selection of delicious food and wines combined with Italian hospitality and service, is where Impero Romano stands for. This all comes together in a new and beautiful location for both lunch and dinner on Amsteldijk 25.

name: De Japanner
description: Looking for the best Japanese restaurant in Amsterdam? Look no further than De Japanner! With an authentic Japanese dining experience, our restaurant offers a variety of Japanese cuisine favorites. Whether you're craving sushi, dumplings or grilled meats, we've got you covered. Conveniently located, De Japanner is the go-to for locals and tourists looking for "Japanese restaurants near me" in Amsterdam. Our diverse menu also makes us a top pick for those searching for the best Asian restaurant in Amsterdam. Visit De Japanner, and experience the taste of Asia right here in the heart of Amsterdam. You won't be disappointed!

name: Sugo
description:
RESTAURANT | DELIVERY | TO-GO

We maken onze pizza iedere dag helemaal met de hand. Rijk aan proteine en geen toegevoegd vet of suiker. Zo wordt de bodem heel licht verteerbaar.
Je kunt bij Sugo iedere dag kiezen uit 20 heerlijke soorten pizza, belegd met topkwaliteit toppings, voornamelijk biologisch. Je herkent onze pizza's direct want... ze zijn vierkant!

Sugo - a new kind of pizza! We make our pizza by hand everyday. They are high in protein and no sugar or fat is added which is why the base is very light and easy to digest. At Sugo you can choose between 20 delicious flavors of pizza with mainly organic toppings that are of the best quality possible. You will recognize a Sugo pizza immediately because... they are square!

name: Taj Indian Restaurant
description:
Taj Indian Restaurant has swiftly emerged as a beloved destination for both locals and visitors in Amsterdam. With its commitment to serving authentic Indian cuisine in a welcoming ambiance, Taj Indian Restaurant offers an unparalleled experience for those craving a taste of India. Conveniently situated at Marie Heineken Plein 1, the restaurant welcomes guests daily from 4:00 PM to 11:00 PM.
Step into our inviting space, where the aroma of simmering spices and the warmth of genuine hospitality embrace you. Whether you're yearning for a nostalgic taste of home or embarking on a culinary adventure, Taj Indian Restaurant is your sanctuary.
we look forward to welcoming you with open arms and tantalizing Flavors.
Taj Amsterdam !

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURYci1fd2lnRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Waew K.","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105051476094893891961?hl=en-GB","review_text":"If you're on the hunt for top-notch seafood in Amsterdam, Brut de Mer is a gem you don't want to miss! Their oyster selection is truly impressive, with six different types to explore, each more delicate and fresh than the last. Pairing them with one of their many crisp white wines or a glass of cava is a must--it elevates the whole experience.

Moving on to the mains, the roasted razor clams and sauteed white clams were spot on. The flavors were bold but balanced, and the texture was just perfect. The calamari, though, might be the hidden hero--it's probably the best I've had in Amsterdam. It's got that tender, melt-in-your-mouth quality and comes with a sauce that's so rich and flavorful that you'll be wiping the plate clean.

Then came the egg with caviar, and wow--it's a dish to remember. Luxurious, silky, and full of flavor, it felt like a little celebration of everything you could want in a seafood meal. The salad dishes were fresh and light, acting as the perfect counterbalance to the richness of the seafood.

The prices are admittedly on the steep side, but for a special occasion, Brut de Mer feels absolutely worth it. Plus, the friendly and attentive staff really add to the vibe, making the whole experience feel like a treat. If you're looking to indulge, this spot will hit all the right notes!","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-01T08:15:57","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOoFXhv_I6209VwfnBN7BU7w9oesY2kMF6lxfdg=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOBXg4tjc-6sFpf_SUN6tIbmY8IzJZsIfJMxvZg=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP5xr4fipIoLInK5O9o0uEwMF8OnMWhfqKqh1Ba=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMueObGcrDwnC5SQ4fQ87q39DWG__ZxnUYvlgws=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMc6Ea6RZdIPTeq8FHK0bz37JrnfSz3jQ-Eq-p3=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMsvmAN45PsmOHHB5MgLe0eks8CAI1jNbWoGaUk=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOIbji15JbXIiev3ja5jZissQdvYdxvLP13bM8t=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOp7_lHmLNgpgSTXuFufDB2zDnk2E-Vm96E7G1p=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURudk5yUVFnEAE","rating":5,"name":"Daniel Chak","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114188313514327272263?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Amazing seafood with a great vibe. name: Renato's Osteria - De Pijp
description:
Renato's Osteria biedt een eenvoudig maar krachtig menu, waar de kwaliteit van de ingredienten en de passie van onze chef-koks elkaar ontmoeten en magie creeren. Ons menu verandert het hele jaar door om verse en seizoensgebonden gerechten voor te stellen.

 Renato's Osteria offers a simple but powerful menu, where the quality of the ingredients and the passion of our chefs meet, creating magic. Our menu changes throughout the year to propose fresh and seasonal dishes.

When you enter the restaurant, it immediately feels very welcoming and the vibe is very friendly, almost like when you visit a local bar.
The staff was super friendly and took our orders really fast.
When I saw the menu, my eyes went directly to the triple cheese burger.
I love cheese but I'm always a little bit worried if the burger is gonna come out soggy or greasy because of all the cheese.

featured_reviews:
[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURYOFpMd3VRRRAB","rating":2,"name":"Fabien-Olivier Girard","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111932744646021866396?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I had high hopes for this Italian restaurant that I pass by every week, but unfortunately, it didn't meet expectations.

The burrata was decent, but at EU17.5, it was a simple dish with cherry tomatoes sliced in 2--overpriced for what it was.
Surprised to be charged for tap water for my daughter (EU1,5), which felt unnecessary.
The Negroni (EU11) seemed hastily made, lacking attention to detail, no garnish (at least a slice of orange would do the job)
The entrecote, which I ordered rare, arrived overcooked and was quite small for the EU32 price tag. The quality of the meat was also not up to par.
They served focaccia without asking, and I was charged EU8.5 for it.
EU11 for a simple vanilla ice cream, counted as an affogato, felt excessive.

The waiter was very pushy with extras, which of course reflected in the final bill. The one highlight was the nice chef, who made an excellent bolognese--delicious, well-served.
Sadly, the overall experience felt like being in a tourist trap where the goal is to pad the bill with unnecessary extras.","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-10-28T14:09:46","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOMYGuMX5yaMXWXdQRCwkOt18bt_tvYXHfu7UGS=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOghalp8Dg3F94Qw1W2DTgsMEtofMlIiNm9yY7i=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMch-FgSC0xD6GqMool_fynNI2i0m4c89ucJ6IL=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNvpId_IxlvAcMs8sq6JSy58ea_kICPm9IOGRzP=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUN2X2JYQjh3RRAB","rating":5,"name":"Jimi Hong","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111407703984569018985?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Why does this place not have higher ratings? name: Poppy's Restaurant de Pijp
description: Poppy's Restaurant de Pijp is a cozy and colourful restaurant in the heart of Amsterdam de Pijp. A favourite amongst locals and visitors of the city for delicious shared dining dishes that are inspired from all over the world. Swing by and choose from a wide array of drinks like our homemade cocktails, fresh juices or wines to enjoy on the beautiful terrace or amongst the flowers inside the restaurant and cafe. Whether you're looking for a restaurant in de Pijp Amsterdam, a cocktailbar in de Pijp or craving our famous Amsterdam high tea, Poppy's is here for you! We plate up our famous lunch during the weekends and our venue is highly suited for any specials events such as bridal events, babyshowers, family gatherings and birthdays.

This is definitely one of my favorite restaurants, we'll be back!","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-10-14T20:10:19","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP2V9zw7B-_B72FfATw0Iic6oHBatRr_r3NMHFn=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipO426JDDBK_tQOFdmEuCYfUTqOqLuloE6iNpTBc=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMQbOXj9XInO58XMpL5Ajp3N56Mvp3vAObbneZN=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNmNXJxTVNREAE","rating":1,"name":"Kim Kuro","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104507260902402757051?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I recently had lunch at IZAKAYA Amsterdam with my partner. I chose the restaurant due to its overwhelmingly positive reviews, but as an Asian, I was truly disappointed by the experience. It felt like a stereotypical Western, cheap take on what Asian food should be, and most dishes did not justify the price tag.

Food: 1 star 

Every dish was more disappointing than the last. Let's start with the basics: they provided us with poorly made disposable chopsticks in what is supposed to be a luxurious, high-class restaurant. Not only were the chopsticks low-quality, but they also left splinters after being split. I've had better ones with cheap Chinese takeout.

Salmon, Yellowtail, and Seabass Sashimi - 24 euro -  1 star

This dish consisted of six thinly sliced pieces of fish heavily drenched in soy sauce with a hint of yuzu aroma, topped with green onion, ginger, and loads of sesame. The flavor profile worked slightly for the seabass, reminding me of Cantonese-style steamed fish. However, it completely ruined the yellowtail and salmon. The richness and fattiness of the fish were overpowered, leaving a dish that was far too salty and dominated by soy sauce.

Salmon Avocado Uramaki (20.5 euro) / Shrimp Tempura Uramaki (19.5 euro) -  3 stars

These were the most ordinary dishes out of all we tried. They weren't bad, but there was nothing special about them in terms of presentation or taste. You can get the same quality at any average Western sushi shop. The rice was too wet and soft, and the rolls were somewhat sticky, but overall, these were the best dishes of the meal.

Beef Toban Hibachi - 34 euro -  1 star

This dish featured six pieces of beef drenched in the same soy sauce with a hint of yuzu aroma, served on a hot plate. The outside of the meat was dry, chewy, and overly salty, while the inside was softer but tasteless. Eating it altogether resulted in a strange combination of overly salty and flavorless at the same time. The enoki mushrooms and single broccoli floret on the plate were also far too salty from being soaked in the sauce. Ironically, the single mushroom and single asparagus were the most delicious elements of the dish.

Ribeye with Anticucho Sauce - 44 euro -  1 star

The anticucho sauce tasted like yellow mustard mixed with taco seasoning and was drizzled over sliced ribeye rather than being grilled with it. The steak's texture was tender enough, but there was no caramelization or grilling that was detectable, leaving it overly saucy and salty. The beef itself was bland and lacked any depth of flavor.

Tea (Jasmine/Matcha) - 5.5 euro each -  2 stars

The tea was just a teabag served in a fancy teapot that didn't appear very clean. Even after half an hour of steeping, the matcha tea still had no flavor.

Service: 4 stars 

I deducted one star because of how understaffed they were. We visited on a Saturday lunchtime, and there was only one host, two waitresses, and a bartender managing the entire floor. While the host was nice and greeted us with a big smile, that's where the positives ended. There was an excessive amount of waiting between everything due to the lack of staff.

We had initially planned to order more after the first round, but given how disappointing everything was, we decided to leave. This was truly a letdown, and I would not recommend this restaurant. There are so many better options in Amsterdam for authentic, well-made Japanese food.","published_at":"2 weeks ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-28T16:54:02","response_from_owner_text":"Dear  Kim ,

I chose the Izakaya set menu (EUR85 p.p), but I dont think the food-quality-price ratio is balanced.
Side note: ''Wagyu'' only means ''beef'', not the Ax grading that is popular. The dumplings were underwhelming. The spinach salad serves 2 pcs of shrimps, 1 per person.

The server whom took our order, his breath reeked of bile/puke as if they had a bad incident prior to coming to our table. This put off my appetite. Then upon taking our order, I asked about the fruits served together with the dessert due to my allergy to stone fruits. He was dismissive by responding: ''Its just a little bit'' ''Oh, but your partner can eat it for you'' ''Oh don't worry about it, its fine''. An allergy is an allergy and should be taken seriously.

The dishes were underwhelming and were overshadowed by the amount of Yuzu (citrus fruit) used in majority of the dishes. In the end, all we could taste was the Yuzu almost to the point of developing a Yuzu-phobia. When finishing the course menu, my partner jokingly mentioned that we are dining at Yuzu-kaya.

The atmosphere was welcoming and in general, the staff were attentive. Japanese-South american fusion was a nice attempt.
